  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Enhancing Literature Review Quality with Machine LearningResearch on the application of machine learning techniques to improve the quality of literature reviews has revealed promising outcomes.",
    "Those techniques have been utilized to categorize and cluster research articles more effectively, facilitating a more organized review process [17,23].",
    "Machine learning models have also been applied to predict the relevance of articles, thereby improving the efficiency of literature search and selection [16,22,24].",
    "The ability of these models to learn from vast datasets and identify patterns has been particularly beneficial for systematic reviews, where the volume of potentially relevant literature can be overwhelming [25,26].",
    "Furthermore, the use of natural language processing has enabled the extraction of key concepts and relationships from texts, enhancing the depth of analysis in literature reviews [27]."
  ],
